RESOURCE.STRING: Open Loop Mode Lock-In Test
This test will temporarily lock the engine control system into an open loop mode of operation and eliminate any feedback from the heated oxygen sensor.

Initial Conditions 1. Engine running 2. No active air to fuel ratio related faults Steps 1. Select Start Additional Information 1. This test will run until Stop is selected 2. When the test is stopped the engine will return to normal operation
Status
The Open Loop Mode Lock-In test is not supported by the current calibration.
No Engine Speed detected. Start the engine and restart the test.
Faults related to air to fuel ratio calculations detected. Troubleshoot active faults before proceeding with this test.
The Engine Control System is locked in an Open Loop Mode of operation. To change the operation mode back to Open/Closed Loop (Normal) Mode select Stop.
The Open/Close Loop (Normal) mode is the default setting. Select Start to set the Engine Control System to the Open Loop Mode.
The ECM detects a condition in which the Open Loop Lock-In Test cannot be run.
Engine Operating Mode
Open/Closed Loop (Normal) Mode
Open Loop
